<p><span style="font-size: small;"><span id="coordinates"><a href="/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system" title="Geographic coordinate system">Coordinates</a>: <span class="plainlinks nourlexpansion"><a class="external text" href="//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Cwmavon%2C_Neath_Port_Talbot&amp;params=51.615511_N_-3.771745_E_region:GB_type:city(6538)"><span class="geo-nondefault"><span class="geo-dms" title="Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location"><span class="latitude">51°36′56″N</span> <span class="longitude">3°46′18″W</span></span></span><span class="geo-multi-punct">﻿ / ﻿</span><span class="geo-default"><span class="geo-dec" title="Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location">51.615511°N 3.771745°W</span><span style="display:none">﻿ / <span class="geo">51.615511; -3.771745</span></span></span></a></span></span></span></p>
<p><b>Cwmavon</b> (<a href="/wiki/Welsh_language" title="Welsh language">Welsh</a>: <span lang="cy" xml:lang="cy"><i>Cwmafan</i></span>) is a large <a href="/wiki/Village" title="Village">village</a> and <a href="/wiki/Community_(Wales)" title="Community (Wales)">community</a> in the <a href="/wiki/River_Afan" title="River Afan">Afan valley</a> in <a href="/wiki/Wales" title="Wales">Wales</a>, lying within <a href="/wiki/Neath_Port_Talbot" title="Neath Port Talbot">Neath Port Talbot County Borough</a>. It has a population of 5,603,<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> increasing slightly to 5,615 at the 2011 Census. In many ways it is a suburb of the nearby <a href="/wiki/Town" title="Town">town</a> of <a href="/wiki/Port_Talbot" title="Port Talbot">Port Talbot</a> which is less than 2 miles (3.2&#160;km) to the south, but it is separated from the town by the local geography. The <a href="/wiki/Literal_translation" title="Literal translation">literal translation</a> of <i>Cwmafan</i> from <a href="/wiki/Welsh_language" title="Welsh language">Welsh</a> to <a href="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">English</a> is 'Valley of the River Afan', <i>Cwm</i> meaning valley and <i>Afan</i> being the name of the river.</p>
<p></p>
